Completeness / depth policy:
- A draft is NOT approved if it is obviously shallow: fewer than {{ min_substantive_sections }}
  substantive `sections` (where substantive means non-empty section `content` prose),
  a markdown body under ~{{ min_markdown_chars }} characters, or sections that are only
  headings without prose. In those cases, do not approve even if citations look fine.
- If the underlying findings appear rich enough to expand, emit a directive
  beginning with "expand:" describing which sections need more depth. The system
  will route back to the synthesizer for another pass.
- If the findings themselves are too thin to support a full report, emit a
  directive beginning with "evidence:" so the system can gather more evidence.
- If unverified_claims or closure_violations are non-empty, include at least one
  directive beginning with "evidence:".

Return JSON matching the critique schema with:
- score (0-5)
- approved (bool)
- directives (list of concrete revision instructions; each prefixed with
  "expand:", "evidence:", or another clear verb)
- rubric object
